    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="211"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1296</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="94" xml:id="d211fn94">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Consul General in his despatch No. 1560, September 10, 1930; received
                        October 8.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-10">September 10,
                            1930</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">L. No. 1055</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith, as of
                    possible interest, a copy of a letter addressed by me under date of September
                    10, 1930, to Mr. W. Russell Brown,<note n="93" xml:id="d211fn93">Not
                        printed.</note> Acting British Consul General at Hankow, by way of an
                    expression of appreciation for the service rendered to several American citizens
                    who evacuated from Changsha during the recent trouble there and who were brought
                    to Hankow on board H. M. S. <hi rend="italic">Aphis</hi>. The letter explains
                    itself.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">F. P. Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
